RE: What Do Christians Have Against Masturbation? (30-12-2012 04:36 PM)germanyt Wrote: It is a sin because it is self-satisfying.
I've never heard that from a Christian, and that's probably a good thing because it's easy to tear apart. Is your claim that all self-satisfying behavior is sinful, or do you hold masturbation to a double-standard? If I play solitaire for example, am I sinning? If I eat a cookie, am I sinning? How about when I scratch an itch?
To be totally honest, I've never heard a Christian explain why it's a sin. They just assume you should know better.
